Sentencas: A Fe-22Cr mesh was dipped into a ceramic (LaNi0.6M0.4O3-delta; M: Co, Fe) slurry to form a metallic/ceramic material as contact coating for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Laser machining of LaNi0.6M0.4O3_δ (M: Co, Fe) dip-coated on a Fe-22Cr mesh material to obtain a new contact coating for SOFC: Interaction between Crofer22APU interconnect and La0.6Sr0.4FeO3 cathode

Sentencas: This composite was directly adhered to a Crofer22APU channeled interconnect and micro-holes were performed on coating using a femtosecond laser.
Titulo: Laser machining of LaNi0.6M0.4O3_δ (M: Co, Fe) dip-coated on a Fe-22Cr mesh material to obtain a new contact coating for SOFC: Interaction between Crofer22APU interconnect and La0.6Sr0.4FeO3 cathode

Sentencas: Then, La0.6Sr0.4FeO3 (LSF) cathode was spray deposited on top of this ablated system to analyze the formed structures in terms of the electrical performance, processing reproducibility and long-term behavior at 800 degrees C.
Titulo: Laser machining of LaNi0.6M0.4O3_δ (M: Co, Fe) dip-coated on a Fe-22Cr mesh material to obtain a new contact coating for SOFC: Interaction between Crofer22APU interconnect and La0.6Sr0.4FeO3 cathode

Sentencas: The adequate reproducibility of the process was confirmed through area specific resistance (ASR) testing on four replicas for each system.
Titulo: Laser machining of LaNi0.6M0.4O3_δ (M: Co, Fe) dip-coated on a Fe-22Cr mesh material to obtain a new contact coating for SOFC: Interaction between Crofer22APU interconnect and La0.6Sr0.4FeO3 cathode

Sentencas: After long-term treatment, the chromium diffusion within both the interconnect and mesh of the composite was quantitatively analyzed using energy dispersive X-ray spectroscopy (EDX).
Titulo: Laser machining of LaNi0.6M0.4O3_δ (M: Co, Fe) dip-coated on a Fe-22Cr mesh material to obtain a new contact coating for SOFC: Interaction between Crofer22APU interconnect and La0.6Sr0.4FeO3 cathode

Sentencas: The laser irradiated composite showed short-range damage, which was limited to the formation of iron and chromium oxides due to the evaporation and oxidation of the mesh.
Titulo: Laser machining of LaNi0.6M0.4O3_δ (M: Co, Fe) dip-coated on a Fe-22Cr mesh material to obtain a new contact coating for SOFC: Interaction between Crofer22APU interconnect and La0.6Sr0.4FeO3 cathode
